    <node id="WINDOW OPENING (BUS IN MOTION)">
      <data key="d0">WINDOW OPENING (BUS IN MOTION)</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Opening bus windows to enhance natural ventilation and increase air changes per hour (ACH) while the bus is moving.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VENTILATION FANS SET TO EXHAUST MODE">
      <data key="d0">VENTILATION FANS SET TO EXHAUST MODE</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Configuring both front and rear bus ventilation fans to exhaust air, which increases ACH compared with supply mode.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="VENTILATION FANS SET TO SUPPLY MODE">
      <data key="d0">VENTILATION FANS SET TO SUPPLY MODE</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Configuring both front and rear bus ventilation fans to supply air; associated with lower ACH than exhaust mode.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="FRONT AND REAR WINDOW PAIR OPEN">
      <data key="d0">FRONT AND REAR WINDOW PAIR OPEN</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Opening one front and one rear window simultaneously; yields higher ACH than opening two rear windows.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="TWO REAR WINDOWS OPEN">
      <data key="d0">TWO REAR WINDOWS OPEN</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Opening two windows located at the rear of the bus; produces lower ACH than a front-rear window pair.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.5</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="AC UNIT EQUIPPED WITH APPROPRIATE PREFILTER">
      <data key="d0">AC UNIT EQUIPPED WITH APPROPRIATE PREFILTER</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Adding a suitable prefilter to the bus air conditioning unit to trap aerosol particles and reduce their spread.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
