      <data key="d0">AIR CHANGES PER HOUR (ACH) IN ROUTE BUS</data>
      <data key="d1">DOSE_OR_RATE</data>
      <data key="d2">Ventilation rate metric measured in the bus; increases with vehicle speed and number/location of open windows, and is higher with fans in exhaust mode.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="92% REDUCTION IN AVERAGE INFECTION RISK WITH WINDOWS OPEN (MOVING BUS)">
      <data key="d0">92% REDUCTION IN AVERAGE INFECTION RISK WITH WINDOWS OPEN (MOVING BUS)</data>
      <data key="d1">EFFECTIVENESS_MEASURE</data>
      <data key="d2">Average infection risk reduced by 92% when the bus is moving with windows open compared to windows closed, per modified Wells–Riley calculations.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.9</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="35% REDUCTION IN AVERAGE INFECTION RISK WITH EXHAUST FAN OPERATION (WINDOWS CLOSED, MOVING BUS)">
      <data key="d0">35% REDUCTION IN AVERAGE INFECTION RISK WITH EXHAUST FAN OPERATION (WINDOWS CLOSED, MOVING BUS)</data>
      <data key="d1">EFFECTIVENESS_MEASURE</data>
      <data key="d2">Average infection risk reduced by 35% when the bus is moving with windows closed and both ventilation fans set to exhaust.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.8</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="PARTICLES SPREAD AT ~50% OF CO2 RATE WITH AC ON (PREFILTER EFFECT)">
      <data key="d0">PARTICLES SPREAD AT ~50% OF CO2 RATE WITH AC ON (PREFILTER EFFECT)</data>
      <data key="d1">EFFECTIVENESS_MEASURE</data>
      <data key="d2">With the air conditioning on, particle spread rate is about half that of CO2, consistent with particle capture by an AC prefilter.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.6</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="ROUTE BUS FIELD MEASUREMENTS AND MODIFIED WELLS–RILEY MODELING">
      <data key="d0">ROUTE BUS FIELD MEASUREMENTS AND MODIFIED WELLS–RILEY MODELING</data>
      <data key="d1">VALIDATION_STUDY</data>
      <data key="d2">Study determining ACH and advection–diffusion of CO2 and particles in a route bus and estimating infection risk using a modified Wells–Riley equation.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.7</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_2</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
    <node id="OPEN WINDOWS">
      <data key="d0">OPEN WINDOWS</data>
      <data key="d1">ENGINEERING_CONTROL</data>
      <data key="d2">Opening bus windows is a ventilation control that increases exchange with outdoor air, raising air changes per hour (ACH) and diluting airborne contaminants in the cabin.</data>
      <data key="d3">0.86</data>
      <data key="d4">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee_chunk_4</data>
      <data key="d5">e45568c3-e22e-4830-92f5-64de955e8aee</data>
    </node>
